<span id="cb1-230"><a href="#cb1-230" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="fu">cat</span>(<span class="st">&quot;</span></span>
<span id="cb1-231"><a href="#cb1-231" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">-----------------------------------------------------------------------</span></span>
<span id="cb1-232"><a href="#cb1-232" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">Glossary (beginner-friendly)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-233"><a href="#cb1-233" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">-----------------------------------------------------------------------</span></span>
<span id="cb1-234"><a href="#cb1-234" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">stages:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-235"><a href="#cb1-235" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Ordered vector of life-history stages used throughout (3 stages here).</span></span>
<span id="cb1-236"><a href="#cb1-236" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  1 = one-leaf, nonflowering; 2 = multileaf, nonflowering; 3 = multileaf, flowering.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-237"><a href="#cb1-237" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-238"><a href="#cb1-238" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">T (transition matrix u_ji):</span></span>
<span id="cb1-239"><a href="#cb1-239" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  3x3 matrix; entry (j,i) is the probability that a plant in stage i at</span></span>
<span id="cb1-240"><a href="#cb1-240" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  year t will be in stage j at year t+1 (including staying in the same</span></span>
<span id="cb1-241"><a href="#cb1-241" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  stage, moving up, or moving down). Rows sum &lt;= 1; columns describe</span></span>
<span id="cb1-242"><a href="#cb1-242" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  fates of each source stage. (Table 2.)  [Yonezawa 2000]</span></span>
<span id="cb1-243"><a href="#cb1-243" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-244"><a href="#cb1-244" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">D_observed, D_expected:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-245"><a href="#cb1-245" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Fractions of the population in each stage (observed vs equilibrium).</span></span>
<span id="cb1-246"><a href="#cb1-246" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Expected values come from the equilibrium of the projection system.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-247"><a href="#cb1-247" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-248"><a href="#cb1-248" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">u_survival (u·i):</span></span>
<span id="cb1-249"><a href="#cb1-249" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Annual survival probabilities by stage (Table 2): probability that an</span></span>
<span id="cb1-250"><a href="#cb1-250" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  individual in stage i survives (to any stage) to the next year.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-251"><a href="#cb1-251" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-252"><a href="#cb1-252" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">Fvec (F_i):</span></span>
<span id="cb1-253"><a href="#cb1-253" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Newborns per plant for each stage (Table 2). In this model, newborns</span></span>
<span id="cb1-254"><a href="#cb1-254" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  recruit to Stage 1. We also provide F as a 3x3 matrix with row 1 = F_i.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-255"><a href="#cb1-255" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-256"><a href="#cb1-256" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">r (r_i) and recruitment_rate:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-257"><a href="#cb1-257" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  r_i are the contributions of newborns to the whole population from</span></span>
<span id="cb1-258"><a href="#cb1-258" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  parents in stage i in that year; sum(r_i) is the total recruitment rate.</span></span>
<span id="cb1-259"><a href="#cb1-259" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-260"><a href="#cb1-260" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">L (generation time):</span></span>
<span id="cb1-261"><a href="#cb1-261" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Average generation length consistent with the stage-structured model</span></span>
<span id="cb1-262"><a href="#cb1-262" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  used in the paper. (Reported in Table 4.)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-263"><a href="#cb1-263" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-264"><a href="#cb1-264" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">Ny_over_N:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-265"><a href="#cb1-265" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  </span><span class="sc">\&quot;</span><span class="st">Annual</span><span class="sc">\&quot;</span><span class="st"> effective population size measured per year (Ny) relative to the</span></span>
<span id="cb1-266"><a href="#cb1-266" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  census size N. Larger Ny/N implies less genetic drift per year. (Table 4.)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-267"><a href="#cb1-267" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-268"><a href="#cb1-268" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">Ne_over_N:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-269"><a href="#cb1-269" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  </span><span class="sc">\&quot;</span><span class="st">Generation-time</span><span class="sc">\&quot;</span><span class="st"> effective population size (Ne) relative to N—captures</span></span>
<span id="cb1-270"><a href="#cb1-270" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  drift across a full generation. (Table 4.)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-271"><a href="#cb1-271" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-272"><a href="#cb1-272" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">Min_N_for_Ne5000:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-273"><a href="#cb1-273" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Minimum census size required to achieve Ne = 5000, given the observed</span></span>
<span id="cb1-274"><a href="#cb1-274" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Ne/N ratio (Table 4).</span></span>
<span id="cb1-275"><a href="#cb1-275" tabindex="-1"></a></span>
<span id="cb1-276"><a href="#cb1-276" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">H_mean, H_sd:</span></span>
<span id="cb1-277"><a href="#cb1-277" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">  Average heterozygosity (± SD) across assayed loci. (Table 4.)</span></span>
<span id="cb1-278"><a href="#cb1-278" tabindex="-1"></a><span class="st">-----------------------------------------------------------------------</span></span>
